#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:330
#, no-c-format
msgid "Fill-in-the-blank"
msgstr "Udfyld-de-blanke"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:332
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "'Fill-in-the-blank' is a powerful way to practice in &kwordquiz;. It is a "
#| "special kind of question and answer quiz that needs to be described in "
#| "more detail. In order to use this feature you must turn it on in the "
#| "<link linkend=\"dlg-config-editor\">configuration dialog</link>."
msgid ""
"'Fill-in-the-blank' is a powerful way to practice in &kwordquiz;. It is a "
"special kind of question and answer quiz that needs to be described in more "
"detail."
msgstr ""
"'Udfyld-de-blanke' er en kraftfuld måde at øve sig i &kwordquiz;. Det er en "
"særlig slags spørgsmål og svar quiz der vil blive beskrevet mere "
"detaljeret.  For at bruge denne funktion skal du slå den til i <link linkend="
"\"dlg-config-editor\">indstillingsdialogen</link>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:336
#, no-c-format
msgid "Consider the following table. It could be a vocabulary in &kwordquiz;:"
msgstr "Betragt følgende tabel. Det kunne være et ordforråd i  &kwordquiz;:"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:344
#, no-c-format
msgid "English"
msgstr "Engelsk"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:345
#, no-c-format
msgid "German"
msgstr "Tysk"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:351
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>1</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>1</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:352 index.docbook:358 index.docbook:364 index.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "We own a computer"
msgstr "Vi ejer en computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:353
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir besitzen einen Computer"
msgstr "Wir besitzen einen Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>2</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>2</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:359
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen] einen Computer"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen] einen Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>3</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>3</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:365
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen einen] Computer"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen einen] Computer"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:369
#, no-c-format
msgid "<entry>4</entry>"
msgstr "<entry>4</entry>"

#. Tag: entry
#: index.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "Wir [besitzen] einen [Computer]"
msgstr "Wir [besitzen] einen [Computer]"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:377
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The important thing to note is the placement of the brackets. They tell "
"&kwordquiz; how the quiz should be performed."
msgstr ""
"Det vigtige er at notere sig placeringen af parenteserne. De fortæller "
"&kwordquiz; hvordan quizzen skal udføres."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:380
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 1. there are no brackets. Assuming English is the question and German the "
"answer you have to give the entire expression 'Wir besitzen einen Computer' "
"for a correct answer."
msgstr ""
"I 1. er der ingen parenteser. Antagende at dansk er spørgsmålet og tysk "
"svaret skal du indgive hele udtrykket 'Wir besitzen einen Computer' for et "
"rigtigt svar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In 2. &kwordquiz; would display the question but also 'Wir ........ einen "
"Computer'. For a correct answer it is sufficient to write 'besitzen'."
msgstr ""
"I 2. &kwordquiz; vil spørgsmålet blive vist men også 'Wir ........ einen "
"Computer'. For et rigtigt svar er det nok at skrive 'besitzen'."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"3. shows that a blank can consist of more than one word. The correct answer "
"is 'besitzen einen'."
msgstr ""
"3. viser at en blank kan bestå af mere end et ord. Det rigtige svar er "
"'besitzen einen'."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:389
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "In 4. there are two separate blanks. To specify that in the answer you "
#| "have to write 'besitzen; Computer', i.e separate the blanks with a "
#| "semicolon in order to get a correct answer."
msgid ""
"In 4. there are two separate blanks. To specify that in the answer you have "
"to write 'besitzen; Computer', &ie; separate the blanks with a semicolon in "
"order to get a correct answer."
msgstr ""
"I 4. er der to adskilte blanke. For at angive det i svaret skal du skrive "
"'besitzen; Computer', dvs adskille de blanke med et semikolon for at få et "
"rigtigt svar."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:392
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "Marked blanks are only of relevance if they appear in the answer. "
#| "Otherwise the brackets are ignored. Furthermore, brackets have no effect "
#| "in multiple choice quizzes. To simplify the creation of 'Fill-in-the-"
#| "blank' vocabularies there are toolbar and menu commands to mark and "
#| "unmark blanks. Of course you can also just type the brackets. &kwordquiz; "
#| "checks the syntax. If the text appears in red there is something wrong "
#| "with the brackets and a quiz cannot be started."
msgid ""
"Marked blanks are only of relevance if they appear in the answer. Otherwise "
"the brackets are ignored. Furthermore, brackets have no effect in multiple "
"choice quizzes. To simplify the creation of 'Fill-in-the-blank' vocabularies "
"there are menu commands to mark and unmark blanks. Of course you can also "
"just type the brackets. &kwordquiz; checks the syntax. If the text appears "
"in red there is something wrong with the brackets and a quiz cannot be "
"started."
msgstr ""
"Markerede blanke er kun af relevans hvis de er der i svaret. Ellers bliver "
"parenteserne ignoreret. Parenteser har derudover ingen virkning i multiple "
"choice quiz. For at simplificere oprettelsen af 'Udfyld-de-blanke' ordforråd "
"er der værktøjslinje- og menukommandoer til at markere og afmarkere blanke. "
"Du kan naturligvis også blot skrive parenteserne. &kwordquiz; tjekker "
"syntaksen. Hvis teksten er rød er der noget galt med parenteserne og en quiz "
"kan ikke startes."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:398
#, no-c-format
msgid "Printing"
msgstr "Udskriver"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:399
#, fuzzy, no-c-format
#| msgid ""
#| "&kwordquiz; provides the ability to print vocabulary documents in several "
#| "different ways. When selecting <menuchoice><guimenu>File</"
#| "guimenu><guimenuitem>Print...</guimenuitem></menuchoice> you are "
#| "presented with the standard &kde; print dialog. In order to get access to "
#| "the special &kwordquiz; features you need to click on the "
#| "<guibutton>Options&gt;&gt;</guibutton> to see the Vocabulary Options tab. "
#| "On this tab you can select to print the document as a vocabulary list "
#| "(&ie; as displayed in the editor), a vocabulary exam, or as flashcards."
